MySql - Class in GUI
This is a very simple example representing how to work with MySQL using java JDBC interface; The example mainly present how to read a table representing a set of WiFi_Scans Note: for simplicity only two properties are stored (in the DB) for each AP: the MAC address (mac) and the signal strength (rssi), the other properties (ssid and channel) are omitted as the algorithms do not use the additional data.
